"The IT Crowd" is a BAFTA and Emmy award-winning British sitcom by Channel 4, written by Graham Linehan, produced by Ash Atalla and starring Richard Ayoade, Chris O'Dowd and Katherine Parkinson.
Set in the London offices of the fictional corporation Reynholm Industries, the show revolves around the three staff members of its IT (information technology) department, comprising two geeky technicians, a genius named Moss (Ayoade) and the workshy Roy (O'Dowd), headed by Jen (Parkinson), the department's 'relationship manager' who knows nothing about IT.
The comedy premiered on Channel 4 on 3 February 2006, and has run for four series of 6 episodes each. A fifth and sixth series have been commissioned.
The show was the third successful sitcom creation of Graham Linehan, following Black Books, co-written with Dylan Moran, and Father Ted, co-written with Arthur Mathews.
